{"parentUuid":"f23feeed-b90c-4a45-8bb0-ea17d245eb9c","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-Administrator","sessionId":"39f469bf-36e8-4ae8-8405-a05a3e6a775f","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmying-gathering-lecun","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PkKyKTenWFedN5sDgpLUso","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me compile the wiring information from the session logs. The key information is:\n\n1. **Current setup**: ESP32 + BSS138 level shifter board (3.3V↔5V bidirectional) on a protoboard\n2. **Problem**: The encoder E40H8-1024-3-T-24 outputs 24V signals, but BSS138 HV side max is 5V\n3. **Solution**: Replace BSS138 with voltage divider (20KΩ + 3.3KΩ) for A and B channels\n\nThe wiring details from the session:\n\n\n- Encoder wire colors: BLACK(A), WHITE(B), ORANGE(Z), BLUE(0V/GND)\n- ESP32 GPIOs: GPIO34 (A channel, connected to LV1), GPIO35 (B channel, connected to LV2)\n- Z channel (ORANGE): not used in code\n- The protoboard has BSS138 modules with LV1/LV2/LV3 and HV1/HV2/HV3 terminals\n\nNow I'll create a clear wiring diagram showing how to replace the BSS138 with the voltage divider circuit for safe signal conversion.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7161,"cache_read_input_tokens":98283,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7161},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYf8YY1xfPnXGGKdXsUDz","type":"assistant","uuid":"75b657fe-8f30-4b42-b78b-cc2b329c0928","timestamp":"2026-03-02T23:35:51.222Z"}
{"parentUuid":"75b657fe-8f30-4b42-b78b-cc2b329c0928","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-Administrator","sessionId":"39f469bf-36e8-4ae8-8405-a05a3e6a775f","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmying-gathering-lecun","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PkKyKTenWFedN5sDgpLUso","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"충분히 파악했습니다. 이전 세션에서 논의된 내용을 정리해드리겠습니다.\n\n---\n\n## 현재 구성\n\n```\n엔코더 E40H8-1024-3-T-24 (출력 24V)\n    ↓\nBSS138 레벨시프터 (HV↔LV, 만능기판)  ← 문제: HV 최대 5V인데 24V 들어옴\n    ↓\nESP32 GPIO34(A), GPIO35(B)\n```\n\n## 전압분배기 배선 (BSS138 대체)\n\n**BSS138 모듈 3개를 만능기판에서 제거**하고, 같은 자리에 저항을 납땜합니다.\n\n### A채널 (엔코더 BLACK선)\n\n```\n엔코더 BLACK(A) ──[20KΩ]──┬── LV1 터미널 → ESP32 GPIO34\n                           │\n                        [3.3KΩ]\n                           │\n                          GND\n```\n\n### B채널 (엔코더 WHITE선)\n\n```\n엔코더 WHITE(B) ──[20KΩ]──┬── LV2 터미널 → ESP32 GPIO35\n                           │\n                        [3.3KΩ]\n                           │\n                          GND\n```\n\n### Z채널 (엔코더 ORANGE선)\n- **미사용** (코드에서 안 씀). 연결 안 해도 됨\n- 이전에 ESP32 리셋 원인으로 의심됐던 채널\n\n### GND (엔코더 BLUE선)\n- ESP32 GND와 **공통 연결 유지** (기존 그대로)\n\n---\n\n## 핵심 요약\n\n| 항목 | 내용 |\n|------|------|\n| **출력 전압** | 24 × 3.3 / (20 + 3.3) = **3.40V** (ESP32 HIGH 인식 OK) |\n| **필요 부품** | 20KΩ 2개 + 3.3KΩ 2개 (1/4W 일반 저항) |\n| **대체 가능** | 20KΩ → **22KΩ**(표준값), 3.3KΩ → **3KΩ** 도 OK (2.5~3.5V면 됨) |\n| **저항 색띠** | 20KΩ = 빨-검-주황-금 / 3.3KΩ = 주황-주황-빨-금 |\n\n## 작업 순서\n\n1. BSS138 모듈 3개 **만능기판에서 제거**\n2. HV 터미널(엔코더 측) → 20KΩ → LV 터미널(ESP32 측) 납땜 (A, B 각 1개)\n3. LV 터미널과 GND 사이에 3.3KΩ 납땜 (A, B 각 1개)\n4. Z채널(ORANGE)은 **아무데도 연결 안 함**\n5. GND 배선 기존 그대로 유지\n6. 엔코더 전원(24V)도 기존 그대로"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7161,"cache_read_input_tokens":98283,"output_tokens":1222,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7161,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYf8YY1xfPnXGGKdXsUDz","type":"assistant","uuid":"dffd796e-d055-4583-b593-8d23333906ea","timestamp":"2026-03-02T23:36:06.886Z"}
